dct_title_s: Syria & Lebanon / published by War Office.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by form lines, hachures, and spot heights. Coordinates are given in grades. Shows international and district boundaries, three classes or roads, roman roads, desert tracks,two classesof  railroads, airfields, oil pipe-lines, roman ruins. "Reprint November 1942." "Copied from a map published by l'Annexe de l'Institut géographique national au Levant, June 1941." "4000/4/42.L.R." Includes comparative table of grades and degrees. "For use by War and Navy Department Agencies only, Not for sale or distribution".
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section
dct_publisher_sm: [London] : War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section, 1942.
